Exercise 03 — GDB Crash Analysis
===================================

The program crashes with a segmentation fault when you run it.
Something, somewhere, goes wrong.

Your goal: use GDB to identify exactly where the crash happens
and why. No [SUCCESS] flag this time — understanding is the goal.

  Run it normally first:
    ./target

  Then load it in GDB and run:
    gdb ./target
    run

  When it crashes, GDB catches it. Inspect the state:
    backtrace
    frame 0
    info registers
    list

  Answer these questions:
    - Which function caused the crash?
    - Which line?
    - What is the value of the pointer being dereferenced?

When you can answer all three AND have read the flag with GDB, submit it: horizon done HRZ{...}
